The charge‑discharge reaction transfers one Li⁺ ion per mole of \(\mathrm{LiCoO_{2}}\) to six carbon atoms of the anode:

\[
\mathrm{LiCoO_{2}}\; \rightleftharpoons\; \mathrm{CoO_{2}}+ \mathrm{Li^{+}}+e^{-}
\qquad
\mathrm{Li^{+}}+6\mathrm{C}\; \rightleftharpoons\; \mathrm{LiC_{6}}
\]

