The complex \([\mathrm{Cr}(\mathrm{NH}_{3})_{6}]^{3+}\) has Cr in the +3 oxidation state.  
Cr\(^{3+}\) has a \(d^{3}\) configuration, giving three unpaired electrons (\(n = 3\)).  

The spin‑only magnetic moment is  

\[
\mu_{\text{so}} = \sqrt{n(n+2)}\;\text{BM}
               = \sqrt{3(3+2)}\;\text{BM}
               = \sqrt{15}\;\text{BM}
               \approx 3.87\;\text{BM}.
\]

\[
\boxed{3.87\ \text{BM}}
\]

The complex \([\mathrm{CuF}_{6}]^{3-}\) has Cu in the +3 oxidation state, giving a \(d^{8}\) configuration.  
In an octahedral field a \(d^{8}\) ion has the electron distribution \(t_{2g}^{6}e_{g}^{2}\), which results in **two unpaired electrons**.

The spin‑only magnetic moment is therefore  

\[
\mu_{\text{so}}=\sqrt{n(n+2)}\;\text{BM}
           =\sqrt{2(2+2)}\;\text{BM}
           =\sqrt{8}\;\text{BM}
           \approx 2.83\;\text{BM}.
\]

\[
\boxed{2.83\ \text{BM}}
